data.description: Modern. Spacious. Usable Yard. Prime Location. This is one of the best priced 4  bedroom homes in sought after Huntingtown. With a lot of the updates done over the last several years, all you need to do is move in and enjoy your new home.  The gem is truly in a prime location. You are districted for Huntingtown school zones and you are in the perfect spot for an easy commute to DC, Annapolis, Andrews AFB, and VA. You are also within about a 5 minute drive to a commuter lot.  It sits on a nice private lot overlooking your neighbors. Concrete steps lead up to your front door, but before we go inside, if you look around you will notice the perfect sitting area out front. Enjoy a fire pit and sip hot chocolate at sunset in your favorite outdoor gliders. The street has no pass-through so tranquility is easily found out front. Inside the home you will notice tons of charming updates including fresh paint, newer flooring, upgraded bathrooms, stainless appliances, newer HVAC and more.  Plenty of parking but you could easily widen or lengthen the driveway as your first Spring project in your new home to get even more spaces. The owners thought about clearing further back to add a nice parking pad for a small RV prior to relocating. When walking in you are greeted with charming shiplap walls along the stairwell. A formal dining room in on your left and the kitchen and living room are wide open. It's the perfect set up for entertaining. Just off the kitchen is a sliding glass door leading to a back deck, perfect for planter boxes and an outdoor table set.  The upper level has 3 great sized bedrooms. One of the three is a spacious primary bedroom with its own en-suite bathroom. Headed to the lower level you will find it mostly finished with a second living room, built in bar, cozy fireplace, a 4th bedroom, and an unfinished laundry room. There is also an unfinished bonus room off the laundry room... perhaps a great space to add a 3rd bathroom later if it's approved! Enjoy this move in ready home and be in before the holidays!
